# ISC Frontend (Vue 3 + Inertia)

## Naming (ISC 1.2)

- Components/pages: `PascalCase.vue` · composables: `useXxx.ts` · utils: `camelCase.ts`
- Constants: `ALL_CAPS` · types/interfaces: `PascalCase`

## Style (ISC 1.3–1.4)

- No magic URLs/timeouts/page sizes — env or shared constants
- One composable/hook = one concern; extract duplicates
- JSDoc on shared utilities and composables

## Security (ISC 1.5)

- No `console.log` of tokens/passwords/OTP
- Never put secrets in `VITE_*` / client bundle — publishable keys only; secrets stay on server
- No raw `v-html` / `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` without sanitization (DOMPurify)
- Safe redirects: only relative paths starting with `/`, not `//`
- Prefer httpOnly cookies or in-memory tokens over `localStorage` for access tokens when possible

## API consumer (ISC 2.x–5.x)

- Handle `success`, `data`, `error`, `meta`; map `error.code` via constants
- Axios/fetch: default timeout; `AbortController` on unmount or when deps change
- Loading, error, and empty states on data views

## UX & performance

- Prefer Inertia visits or TanStack Query-style patterns over ad-hoc fetch+useState when caching matters
- Avoid inline object/array/function props that defeat memoization when hot paths matter
- `useCallback` / `useMemo` where measured; fix stale `useEffect` deps
- Error boundary or Inertia error pages for render failures
- i18n for user-visible strings when i18n is enabled
- Basic a11y: `alt`, real `<button>`, `aria-label` on icon buttons

Full review checklist: `docs/isc-standards-fe.md`.
